The paper deals with training deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The focus on sparse prediction targets and word embeddings also suggests a possible fit with neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Finally, the use of efficient algorithms and optimization techniques is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research, which could also be a relevant sub-category.
